default5. default              defaultThdefaulte legal impact of the Childrendefault Act (1989) case default&#xa0;default5.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultSince the judgment, the case has been cited in over 20 other cases
default 
defaultand has become a key case in the interpretation of children’s rights.  This is because in passing judgment Mr Justice Munby affirmed that 
defaultin his view the rights contained in the United Nations Convention of the Rights of the Child and t
defaulthe European Charter 
defaultcan ‘
defaultproperly be consulted insofar as they proclaim, reaffirm or elucidate the content of those human rights that are generally recognised
default throughout the European family of nations, in particular the nature and scope of those fundamental rights that are guaranteed by the European Convention
default’ (para
defaultgraph
default 51). 
default6. default              defaultWhy was the case brought by the Howard leaguedefault for Penal Reform default&#xa0;default6.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAt the point wh
defaulten the charity brought this claim, it did not provide legal services to young people, as it now does.  However, the charity carefully considered in liaison with expert counsel whether or not this challenge should be brought 
defaultinstead 
defaultof 
defaultby 
defaulta child affected. 
default The charity decided to bring the case as an organization in order to ensure a thorough review of the principles 
defaultin
default issue.  A claim on behalf of an individual child may or may not have arisen
default – that was not an issue that the charity had any control of.  Ho
defaultwever, it would have appeared 
defaultwrong in principle to wait for a child to be at real risk of failures by the system to protect his or her welfare and there would have been a real danger that the litigation would become focused on that individual 
default‘
defaultrisk child
default’
default rather than the systemic issues that affected all children in custody.
