default7.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultUnder the proposed regime, the Howard 
defaultLeague for Penal Reform would have been unable to bring thi
defaults judicial review to court. Even if the 
defaultsafeguarding policies and promotion of safety across the entirety of the secure estate
default had been introduced as a matter of good practice, it would not have ha
defaultd a statutory footing.  Children
default would not be 
defaultentitled to be protected and assessed under the Children Act 1989 while in detention.
default&#xa0;
default7.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe opportunity facilitated by the Howard League for 
defaultPenal
default Reform for the Court to consider these important issues and to c
defaultlarify the law had a major impact on the development of law, policy and practice in 
defaultthis important area.  Any rules to restrict the ability of the Court to determine important issues of law raised by 
defaultorganis
defaultations such as the Howard League for Penal Reform
default should be resisted.  The Courts are best placed to determine these issues and to continue to exercise their discretion wisely and appropriately.
